@node "Updates" "Bug reports & Updates"
@{b}@{u}Bug Reports@{ub}@{uu}

If you have found a bug in F1GP-Ed, contact me via e-mail, or send me a
disk and SAE (or cash equivalent), along with a detailed bug report telling
me what version of F1GP you have (A, B or C) and how you get the bug to
occur. I will then fix the bug (hopefully) as soon as possible and send you
the update. If nobody tells me about any bugs, I'll never be able to fix
them :-(

@{b}@{u}How to obtain updates@{ub}@{uu}

F1GP-Ed is updated regularly so that any bugs can be fixed and new features
implemented.

The latest versions of F1GP-Ed should be available from:

 * PD libraries (you should not pay more than Ł1.50)
 * Aminet ftp sites (game/misc directory) - also Aminet CDs
 * The F1GP-Ed web page - http://cswww2.essex.ac.uk/users/robeoy/F1GP-Ed/

The alternative for @{b}registered users@{ub} in the UK is to send me Ł1, or an
error-free disk and enough stamps to cover return postage.

I can't afford to notify everyone when new updates become available, as the
number of registered users is getting pretty large, and it would just take
too long (this is were e-mail comes in handy!).
@endnode

@node "Author" "The Author"
I'm currently studying Computer Science at the University of Essex in the
UK. As you have probably gathered, I am also a dedicated F1/F1GP/Amiga
addict, otherwise I wouldn`t have bothered writing F1GP-Ed in the first
place :-)

Mail will be forwarded to me if I am at Uni, so please allow an extra
couple of days for a reply - and please supply an SAE if possible.

My permanent home address is:

   30 Tillett Road
   Norwich
   Norfolk
   NR3 4BJ
   ENGLAND

You can contact me via Internet e-mail at this address:

   O.J.C.Roberts@essex.ac.uk

I also have a World Wide Web (WWW) homepage on the Internet.  This is also
the WWW home of F1GP-Ed.  I have created the Amiga Formula One Homepage,
and I also maintain the WWW pages for the F1GP Hall of Fame and the
Internet F1GP Championship.  The Amiga Formula One Homepage also holds all
the Amiga F1GP utilities, Amiga F1GP 2 News, F1GP/WC FAQ, and loads of
other Amiga / Formula One related links.  So set your web browser to:

   http://cswww2.essex.ac.uk/users/robeoy/AmigaF1.html

I can also be found lurking around on Internet Relay Chat (IRC) on the
#Amiga channel with nickname "F1Oli".
@endnode

